   {:e #blake3 "293425c088487ee8a7a756b8ea528e9a51fc48d74e32bf338835c0acfd0d40ce" :a :task/description :v "COMPREHENSIVE VERIFICATION for DAEMON-WRITE migration. SIX TEST CATEGORIES: === CATEGORY 1: SEMANTIC EQUIVALENCE (INV-DAEMON-004) === For each of 11 routable commands: (a) Start daemon, run command through daemon, capture output + store state. (b) Stop daemon, run SAME command in direct mode on identical store copy, capture output + store state. (c) Verify: output text matches (modulo timestamps/PIDs). Store datom counts match. Specific datom entities match. Test matrix: observe (with all flags), harvest (commit), seed, task-create, task-go, task-close, task-ready, write-assert, query, status, guidance. === CATEGORY 2: STALE CACHE ELIMINATION (INV-STORE-020) === (a) Rapid sequential: run 10 braid observe commands rapidly. All 10 appear in final braid status. Zero missing. (b) Interleaved read-write: alternate braid observe and braid status 5 times. Every observation visible in every subsequent status. (c) The IRON TEST: braid task create 'X' → immediately braid task search 'X' → FOUND. This was the original user-reported failure. === CATEGORY 3: CONCURRENT AGENTS (INV-STORE-022) === (a) Fork 3 child processes, each running braid observe with unique text. Wait for all. Run braid status. All 3 observations present. (b) Fork 2 processes: one running braid harvest --commit, one running braid observe. Both complete. Store consistent. === CATEGORY 4: FALLBACK CORRECTNESS === (a) Kill daemon (SIGKILL, not graceful). Run braid observe. Verify: auto-start succeeds OR falls back to direct mode. Observation in store. (b) Run non-routable command (braid bilateral) with daemon running. Verify: uses direct mode (daemon log has no request). (c) Daemon returns error → CLI falls back → command succeeds in direct mode. === CATEGORY 5: PERFORMANCE === (a) braid observe through daemon: < 500ms wall time. (b) braid status through daemon: < 1s wall time (daemon warm). (c) braid observe in direct mode: < 2s wall time. === CATEGORY 6: REGRESSION === cargo test — all existing tests pass (was 2043). === E2E SCRIPT STRUCTURE === Each test script: (1) creates isolated tempdir with braid init. (2) Logs daemon PID, socket path, store path. (3) For each assertion: logs expected value, actual value, datom entity ID, store datom count. (4) On failure: dumps store.bin fingerprint, meta.json, known_hashes, list_tx_hashes diff. (5) Cleanup: stops daemon, removes tempdir. FILES: scripts/e2e_daemon_write.sh (~300 lines), crates/braid/tests/daemon_write.rs (~200 lines)." :op :assert}
